        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued March 31 at 8:48PM EDT until March 31 at 9:15PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 848 PM EDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Stony Creek to near Jarratt to near Green Plain,
moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to trees and powerlines.

These severe storms will be near...
Sussex and Stony Creek around 855 PM EDT.
Homeville around 900 PM EDT.
Waverly around 905 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these severe thunderstorms include Gray,
Grizzard, Newville, Booker, Reams, Yale, Fields Crossroads,
Lumberton, Wharfs Store, and Huske.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
